cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for preserving learned knowledge in neural networks when access to data is restricted, which is a common problem in machine learning. The proposed method involves modeling the high-level feature space and the output space to be mutually informative, and constraining feature vectors to lie in the modeled space during training. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural networks (cs.NE).
